headline.main: TRIBUTE TO DARLAN IS PAID BY STIMSON; War Secretary Says Reports Impress Him With Late Chief's 'Wisdom and Loyalty' ALSO HAILS 'COOPERATION' Hopes French Will Release Full Story When Inquiry on Slaying is Ended

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Dec. 31 -- The investigation of the assassination of Admiral Jean Francois Darlan, which led to the arrest of a dozen persons in Algiers yesterday, and may throw new light upon the political situation in North Africa, is not yet completed, according to a statement by Henry L. Stimson, Secretary of War, today.
abstract: French pol: Sec Stimson lauds Darlan cooperation with Lt Gen Eisenhower; hopes French will release full story when inquiry on Darlan slaying is ended; factors discussed; Gen Giraud warns against divisional factions among French pub; arrest of 12 accused of plotting Giraud and US Min Murphy assassination cited
